    "created_at": "2013-10-26T01:43:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-10-26T01:43:41Z",
    "body": "I'm not really opposed to this, but I'm not sure I'd say it's \"recommended\" to use `externfn!`. The role of `externfn!` is to bridge from extern to Rust (though I guess it could be generalized to \"bridge from ABI to ABI\"). However, if we opt to remove segmented stacks, we wouldn't need `externfn!` at all (it's not clear to me we need it now...)\n",
